<subSubSection id="C329657FFFFAFFECD18C0B809ED3FE09" pageId="13" pageNumber="394" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8C36F4FFFAFFECD18C0B809F9BFF71" blockId="13.[151,538,150,213]" box="[151,249,187,213]" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">
(
<figureCitation id="13082A71FFFAFFECD1BB0B809F93FF71" box="[160,241,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–34" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[165,1421,181,1838]" captionTargetId="figure-18@12.[165,1421,181,1838]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 27–34. 27–28, dorsal view, scale bar 5.0 mm, 27, Heza sericans Stål, 1859, female, 28, Isocondylus elongatus (Lepeletier &amp; Serville, 1825), male; 29–33, Notocyrtus costai Gil-Santana &amp; Forero, 2009; 29–31, female holotype deposited in MZUSP, 29–30, scale bar 2.0 mm, 29, dorsal view, 30, lateral view, 31, labels and right hind leg glued to a card pinned with the specimen; 32–33, female from French Guiana, dorsal view, 32, scale bar 5.0 mm, 33, head, scale bar 1.0 mm; 34, Notocyrtus depressus Stål, 1872, female, dorsal view, scale bar 5.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6332724" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6332724/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8C36F4FFFAFFECD18C0A389ED3FE09" blockId="13.[151,1437,259,502]" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">
Both 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA24B05FFFAFFECD1CE0A389E30FEB9" author="Stal, C." box="[213,338,259,286]" pageId="13" pageNumber="394" pagination="1 - 159" refId="ref13654" refString="Stal, C. (1872) Enumeratio Hemipterorum. Bidrag till en foreteckning ofver alla hittils kanda Hemiptera, jemte systematiska meddelanden. 2. Kongliga Svenska Vetenskaps-Akademiens Handlingar, 10 (4), 1 - 159." type="journal article" year="1872">Stål (1872)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA24B05FFFAFFECD0930A389DC6FEB9" author="Carvalho, J. C. M. &amp; Costa, L. A. A." box="[392,676,259,285]" pageId="13" pageNumber="394" pagination="365 - 384" refId="ref10805" refString="Carvalho, J. C. M. &amp; Costa, L. A. A. (1993) Revision of the known species of Notocyrtus Burmeister, 1835 (Hemiptera-Heteroptera, Reduviidae; Harpactorinae). Revista Brasileira de Biologia, 53, 365 - 384." type="journal article" year="1993">Carvalho &amp; Costa (1993)</bibRefCitation>
described only the female of 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D77FFFAFFECD2EA0A3F9B82FEB9" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1872" box="[1009,1248,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Notocyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="depressus">
<emphasis id="B947EAE6FFFAFFECD2EA0A3F9B82FEB9" box="[1009,1248,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">Notocyrtus depressus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on a 
<typeStatus id="54888856FFFAFFECD4770A3F9AFEFEBA" box="[1388,1436,260,286]" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">type</typeStatus>
specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="F3247664FFFAFFECD0510A1C9EDAFEE5" box="[330,440,295,321]" name="Colombia" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">Colombia</collectingCountry>
deposited in NHRS. Following 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA24B05FFFAFFECD2360A1C9B30FEE5" author="Carvalho, J. C. M. &amp; Costa, L. A. A." box="[813,1106,295,321]" pageId="13" pageNumber="394" pagination="365 - 384" refId="ref10805" refString="Carvalho, J. C. M. &amp; Costa, L. A. A. (1993) Revision of the known species of Notocyrtus Burmeister, 1835 (Hemiptera-Heteroptera, Reduviidae; Harpactorinae). Revista Brasileira de Biologia, 53, 365 - 384." type="journal article" year="1993">Carvalho &amp; Costa (1993)</bibRefCitation>
, the main diagnostic characteristics of 
<taxonomicName id="4C334D77FFFAFFECD00E0A779EC6FEC1" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1872" box="[277,420,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Notocyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="depressus">
<emphasis id="B947EAE6FFFAFFECD00E0A779EC6FEC1" box="[277,420,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">N. depressus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are its general black color, large size and the transversal furrow on the pronotum. The specimen examined here (
<figureCitation id="13082A71FFFAFFECD0E80A549D27FE2D" box="[499,581,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–34" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[165,1421,181,1838]" captionTargetId="figure-18@12.[165,1421,181,1838]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 27–34. 27–28, dorsal view, scale bar 5.0 mm, 27, Heza sericans Stål, 1859, female, 28, Isocondylus elongatus (Lepeletier &amp; Serville, 1825), male; 29–33, Notocyrtus costai Gil-Santana &amp; Forero, 2009; 29–31, female holotype deposited in MZUSP, 29–30, scale bar 2.0 mm, 29, dorsal view, 30, lateral view, 31, labels and right hind leg glued to a card pinned with the specimen; 32–33, female from French Guiana, dorsal view, 32, scale bar 5.0 mm, 33, head, scale bar 1.0 mm; 34, Notocyrtus depressus Stål, 1872, female, dorsal view, scale bar 5.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6332724" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6332724/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
) is a female which matches well with the previous descriptions (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA24B05FFFAFFECD4330A549AFAFE2D" author="Stal, C." box="[1320,1432,367,394]" pageId="13" pageNumber="394" pagination="1 - 159" refId="ref13654" refString="Stal, C. (1872) Enumeratio Hemipterorum. Bidrag till en foreteckning ofver alla hittils kanda Hemiptera, jemte systematiska meddelanden. 2. Kongliga Svenska Vetenskaps-Akademiens Handlingar, 10 (4), 1 - 159." type="journal article" year="1872">Stål 1872</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA24B05FFFAFFECD18C0AA89EC6FE09" author="Carvalho, J. C. M. &amp; Costa, L. A. A." box="[151,420,403,429]" pageId="13" pageNumber="394" pagination="365 - 384" refId="ref10805" refString="Carvalho, J. C. M. &amp; Costa, L. A. A. (1993) Revision of the known species of Notocyrtus Burmeister, 1835 (Hemiptera-Heteroptera, Reduviidae; Harpactorinae). Revista Brasileira de Biologia, 53, 365 - 384." type="journal article" year="1993">Carvalho &amp; Costa 1993</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
